  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "I have a concern about Ethereum sharding. Why is the goal not to abstract away the concept of sharding to the smart contract developer? Traditional database sharding is abstracted, so why not Ethereum sharding? Unnecessary complexity for the developers :(\r\n\r\nI have not been deeply involved in the design of Ethereum sharding, perhaps there are some technical reasons for why this type of abstraction is not being pursued. But, one of the design goals specified in the README of this repository is \"to minimize complexity, even at the cost of some losses in efficiency\". Not abstracting the concept of shards to the developer is going to be a major source of complexity for the developer. I don't understand why this abstraction is not one of the major design goals, and I'd love some elaboration.\r\n\r\nThanks!",
