    "body": "You could take a look at the work of Vlad Zamfir if you're into load-balancing and cross-shard interactions. The current rationale is to keep things simple, as it is already complicated enough to implement sharding and POS. And abstractions for cross-shard interactions can still emerge on a simple protocol design. Take ERC-20 as an example, Ethereum just had to provide the lower ability to implement contracts, and people implemented their own currencies.",
